    <selectionEntry type="upgrade" import="true" name="Munitorum Cherub" hidden="false" id="2772-031f-6d96-99c5">
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="points" value="10"/>
      </costs>
      <profiles>
        <profile name="Munitorum Cherub" typeId="3ce5-e1a1-5b1f-0410" typeName="Wargear" hidden="false" id="7d51-60ea-3739-e8ae">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Description" typeId="14c0-3a47-fe6d-6563">Once per battle, after selecting targets for this unit’s weapons, you may ‘use the blessed ammunition’ and select a model in this unit. If you do, for each attack made for the selected model this turn, reroll a failed Hit and Wound roll for that attack. (Use the Cherub models to note when a unit has yet to use this ability and remove them after the ability is used.)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <constraints>
        <constraint type="max" value="1" field="selections" scope="parent" shared="true" id="179b-5623-bd66-93ba" includeChildSelections="false"/>
